        <h3 style="margin-top: 0px;" id="pop_facts">
            Colorado Springs Population Facts
        </h3>
    


            <h4>What is the current population of Colorado Springs?</h4>
            <p>
                Based on the latest 2022 data from the US census, the
                current population of Colorado Springs is 483,956.  Colorado Springs, Colorado is the 40th largest city in the US.
            </p>

            
                <h4>What county is Colorado Springs, Colorado in?</h4>
                <p>
                
                    Colorado Springs is located entirely in 
                    El Paso County.
                
                </p>
            

            
                
                    <h4>What is the size of Colorado Springs, Colorado in square miles?</h4>
                    Colorado Springs has an area of 
                    194.5 square miles.

                    
                    
                        Colorado Springs is the
                        
                        largest city, by area, in Colorado.
                    
                
            

            <h4>What was the peak population of Colorado Springs?</h4>
            <p>
                
                    The current population of Colorado Springs (483,956) is it's peak population.
                
            </p>
            
                
                    <h4>How quickly is Colorado Springs growing?</h4>
                
                <p>
                    
                        Colorado Springs has grown
                        33.6% 
                        since the 2000.
                    


                    
                        Colorado Springs, Colorado is growing moderately quickly;
                        it is growing faster than 80%
                        of similarly sized cities since 2000.
                    
                </p>
            

            
                <h4>Is Colorado Springs the biggest city in Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                    No, Colorado Springs is the second largest city in the state of Colorado based on population.
                            The biggest city, <a href="/city/denver-colorado">Denver</a>, is 1.5x bigger than Colorado Springs.
                </p>
            

            
                <h4>What is the population density of Colorado Springs, Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                Colorado Springs has a population density of
                2,140.6 people
                per square mile.

                
                
                </p>
            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
