        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="demographics">
            Colorado Springs Demographics
        </h3>
    


            
                

                
                <h4>What is the voting age population of Colorado Springs, Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                    The total voting age population of Colorado Springs, Colorado, meaning US citizens 18 or older, is 341,452.  The voting age population is 49.6% male and 50.4% female.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Colorado Springs, Colorado residents are senior citizens?</h4>
                    <p>
                        According to the latest census statistics, 13.4% of
                        the residents of Colorado Springs are 65 or older.
                    </p>
                

                
                    

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    
                    
                    <h4>What are the racial demographics of Colorado Springs, Colorado?</h4>
                    <p>The racial demographics of Colorado Springs are 78.5% White, 6.5% Black, 5.9% Two or more races, 5.1% Other, 2.9% Asian, 0.8% American Indian and 0.3% Native Hawaiian or Other Pacific Islander. Additionally, 17.6% of the population identifies as Hispanic.</p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Colorado Springs, Colorado residents are below the poverty line?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Colorado Springs, 11.7% of
                    residents have an income below the poverty line, and the child poverty rate
                    is 15.8%.
                    On a per-household basis,
                    8.1% of families are below
                    the poverty line in Colorado Springs.
                    </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Colorado Springs, Colorado residents are in the labor force?</h4>
                    <p>
                    Among those aged 16 and older, 67.4% of
                    Colorado Springs residents are in the labor force.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                <h4>What are the education levels among Colorado Springs, Colorado residents?</h4>
                <p>Among the adult population 25 years old and over,
                    93.9% of
                    Colorado Springs residents have at least a high school degree or
                    equivalent, 39.9%
                    have a bachelor's degree and 15.5%
                    have a graduate or professional degree.
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of Colorado Springs, Colorado residents speak a non-English language at home?</h4>
                <p>
                Among Colorado Springs residents aged 5 and older, 12.8% of them speak a non-English language at home.
                Broken down by language:
                8.3% of residents speak Spanish at home,
                2.1% speak an Indo-European language, and
                1.8% speak an Asian language.

                </p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="labor">
            Colorado Springs Income &amp; Labor Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                    <h4>What is the unemployment rate in Colorado Springs, Colorado?</h4>
                    <p>
                        The unemployment rate in Colorado Springs is 5.7%, which is calculated among residents aged 16 or older who are in the labor force.
                    </p>

                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Colorado Springs, Colorado residents work for the government?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Colorado Springs, 14.5% of the
                    residents in the non-military labor force 
                    are employed by the local, state and federal government.
                    </p>
                

                

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
        <div class="adthrive-content-ad" style="min-height: 120px;">
            
        </div>
    

                
                
                    <h4>What is the median income in Colorado Springs, Colorado?</h4>
                    <p>The median household income in Colorado Springs is $64,712.</p>
                

                
    
        <h3 style="margin-top: 25px;" id="housing">
            Colorado Springs Housing &amp; Rent Statistics
        </h3>
    


                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are owner-occupied in Colorado Springs, Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                    In Colorado Springs, 59.0% of housing units
                    are occupied by their owners.
                </p>
                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of housing units are rented in Colorado Springs, Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                    Renters occupy 41.0% of housing units in
                    Colorado Springs.
                </p>
                

                
                
                    <h4>What percentage of Colorado Springs, Colorado housing units were built before 1940?</h4>
                    <p>
                        Of all the housing units in Colorado Springs,
                        5.8% of them were build before 1940.
                    </p>
                

                
                

                
                    <h4>What percentage of Colorado Springs, Colorado housing units were built after 2000?</h4>
                    <p>
                    In Colorado Springs, 22.2% of the 
                    total housing units were built
                    
                        after the year 2000, which is approximately 
                        
                            42,600 units.
                        
                    
                    </p>
                
                
                
                
                <h4>What is the median monthly rent in Colorado Springs, Colorado?</h4>
                <p>
                    The median gross monthly rent payment for renters in Colorado Springs is
                    $1,131.
                </p>

                

                
                
                <h4>What percentage of households in Colorado Springs, Colorado have broadband internet?</h4>
                <p>
                    In Colorado Springs, 90.2% of households have
                    an active broadband internet connection.
                </p>
                
                
            

            

    
    
        
    

    

    
   
    
